The paper deals with graph sparsification in a streaming setting, which is a problem in graph algorithms and data structures. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves analyzing distributions and graphs, which are topics in cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The use of space and approximation algorithms suggests a connection to cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper deals with social and interaction networks, which are topics in cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper involves graph cuts and connectivity, which are topics in cs.CG (Computational Geometry).
